                            Profession Drops

    With professions come profession materials. If you'd like to have
rooms or npcs have any of the materials as loot, you can.

For Example:
#include <professions.h>
inherit PROFESSION_MATERIAL;

void reset(int iArg)
{
  if(!is_clone(this_object())) return;
  ::reset(iArg);
  if(iArg) return;

  set_short("a bundle of Topaz Shards");
  set_long("\
A small bundle of Topaz Shards used for professions.\n");
  set_aliases(({"bundle","shard","shards","Topaz Shard","Topaz Shards"}));
  set_profession_type("special");
  set_profession_item("Topaz Shard");
  set_profession_quantity(5);
}

    set_profession_type("<type>") must be: bolt, herb, ore, reagent,
skin or special. Lower case, and if not one of those, it will do nothing.

    set_profession_item("<item>") is the profession material. They are case
sensitive to match what you'd see in the reagents command. If it doesn't
match a known item, it will do nothing.

    set_profession_quantity(int) is the quantity to add/subtract from the
player's total when they pick up the item.

    Just like standard reagent drops, the code for applying the count is done
when the player picks up the item using init(). It also gives them random(100)
coins for the item, unless you override it with your own set_value.

    If you want your own special item added to the special list for an area
specific quest or item, please contact an admin to get it added for you.

                         Profession Recipe

    Along with profession drops, you can create recipe cards. The
cards allow the players to create objects with the items they have
gathered.

For Example:
#include <professions.h>
#include "ExampleHeaderFile.h"
inherit PROF_RECIPE;

void reset(int iArg)
{
  if(!is_clone(this_object())) return;
  ::reset(iArg);
  if(iArg) return;

  set_short("Fly Potion Recipe Card");
  set_object_file(PROF_DIR+"potions/fly");
  set_required_items ( ([
    "Hashish":"herb";3,
    "Mistletoe":"herb";3,
   ]) );
  set_other_items ( ([
    "Cow Horn":MYAREAOBJS+"cowhorn";3,
    "The King's favorite beer":MYAREAOBJS+"budlight";3
   ]) );
  set_prof_level_required("Alchemy",1,1);
  set_read_info("\
This recipe creates a Hashish Potion for flight.");
  set_uses(5);
  set_value(50);
}

  set_object_file(filepath) is the path to the object that will be created.

  set_required_items(mapping) is the mapping of the profession materials
needed to create the item. It should be:
([ case-sensitive material short: profession type ; quantity ])

  set_other_itmes(mapping) is the mapping for any other non-profession
materials required to create the item. It should be:
([ string description of the item : object path ; quantity ])
The description could be the short of the item, or a hint to what it is
if it's part of a quest combine, or whatever you want them to see when
they read the card.

  set_prof_level_required("<Profession>", min skill to craft, tNoSkillup).
Profession should be any of the 8 professions. Min skill is the minimum
skill they need in the profession to craft the item. tNoSkillup means
that they can't gain a skillup using the card. If the minimum skill is <= 500,
the max skill they can gain is minimum skill + 100, otherwise 1000.

  set_uses(int) is the amount of times the players can use the card.
